-- Step 5: Observed vs. Null --
  Median observed shared bills:  1.0
  Expected under null (median):  0.045
  Ratio (above null):            22x

  Mean observed shared bills:    2.69
  Expected under null (mean):    0.197
  Ratio (above null):            14x

-- Step 6: Zero-Edge Pairs (no shared bills) --
  Pairs with zero shared bills:  64,382  (88.9%)
  Pairs with shared bills:       8,008  (11.1%)
  → The network is sparse at the global level, but within-community
    overlap is substantially higher — motivating community analysis.

-- Interpretation --
  Co-lobbying is 22x above random chance at the median pair,
  despite the global sparsity. This is the core justification for:
  (1) treating co-lobbying edges as a meaningful coordination signal,
  (2) using community detection to find coordinated lobbying coalitions,
  (3) studying cross-industry connectors (firms bridging coalitions).

  See design_decisions.md §3 for full rationale.
